1
00:00:00,816 --> 00:00:03,351
[NARRATOR] Alchemy...
the science of understanding,

2
00:00:03,351 --> 00:00:05,833
deconstructing, and
reconstructing matter;

3
00:00:05,833 --> 00:00:08,699
however, it is not
an all-powerful art.

4
00:00:08,733 --> 00:00:11,699
It is impossible to create
something out of nothing.

5
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:13,666
If one wishes to
obtain something,

6
00:00:13,699 --> 00:00:16,266
something of equal
value must be given.

7
00:00:16,299 --> 00:00:18,633
This is the Law of
Equivalent Exchange,

8
00:00:18,666 --> 00:00:20,666
the basis of all alchemy.

9
00:00:20,699 --> 00:00:22,066
In accordance with this law,

10
00:00:22,099 --> 00:00:23,833
there is a taboo
among alchemists.

11
00:00:23,866 --> 00:00:26,366
Human transmutation
is strictly forbidden.

12
00:00:26,399 --> 00:00:29,399
For what could equal
the value of a human soul?

13
00:02:03,635 --> 00:02:06,707
[NARRATOR]
Scar, the man who was
responsible for killing

14
00:02:06,707 --> 00:02:10,574
a string of State Alchemists,
came after Edward Elric.

15
00:02:10,607 --> 00:02:13,407
Ed was ready to accept
death at Scar's hand.

16
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,507
But thanks to the intervention

17
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:16,507
of Colonel Mustang
and the military,

18
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:19,707
Ed was able to
escape with his life.

19
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:22,874
Ed and Al, realizing
the joy of being alive,

20
00:02:22,907 --> 00:02:26,407
were once again determined
to survive and move forward.

21
00:02:26,440 --> 00:02:28,840
They decided to return to
their home in Resembool

22
00:02:28,874 --> 00:02:31,707
to seek help in
repairing their bodies.

23
00:02:38,007 --> 00:02:39,374
[KNOCKING]

24
00:02:39,407 --> 00:02:39,940
[ED] Huh...?

25
00:02:39,974 --> 00:02:40,874
Hey.

26
00:02:42,007 --> 00:02:43,707
[ED] Lt. Colonel?

27
00:02:43,740 --> 00:02:45,474
[HUGHES]
The folks at the Eastern
Command Center were

28
00:02:45,507 --> 00:02:47,407
a little too busy to
make it down here today,

29
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,340
so I came to see
you off instead.

30
00:02:49,374 --> 00:02:51,407
Great, but would
you mind telling me...

31
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:53,307
...what the major's
doing here?

32
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,674
For protection...

33
00:02:54,707 --> 00:02:57,007
What would happen if
Scar came after you again?

34
00:02:57,040 --> 00:03:00,407
You're in no shape
for a fight now, Ed.

35
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:01,807
The Major's
here to help.

36
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:03,740
Just try to grin
and bear it.

37
00:03:03,774 --> 00:03:05,440
Children can
be so stubborn.

38
00:03:05,474 --> 00:03:08,074
Hey shut up!
I'm no child!

39
00:03:08,107 --> 00:03:11,074
Anyway... are you sure
Al made it on board?

40
00:03:11,107 --> 00:03:11,807
Of course.

41
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:16,607
[SHEEP BLEAT]

42
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,440
I thought he might get
lonely without a little company.

43
00:03:18,474 --> 00:03:21,374
My brother isn't some
kind of farm animal!

44
00:03:21,407 --> 00:03:23,474
[HUGHES]
Oh... it's time.

45
00:03:23,507 --> 00:03:26,407
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

46
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:28,440
Okay, you boys have a safe trip.

47
00:03:28,474 --> 00:03:29,340
Stop in and give me a shout

48
00:03:29,374 --> 00:03:31,707
the next time you
make it to Central.

49
00:03:48,074 --> 00:03:53,274
[ED SNORES]

50
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,807
[ED YAWNS]

51
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:06,607
[ED YELLLS]

52
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:08,607
[ARMSTRONG]
Doctor Marcoh!

53
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:11,374
Doctor Marcoh,
that is you, isn't it?

54
00:04:11,407 --> 00:04:15,707
It's me! Alex Louis
Armstrong from Central.

55
00:04:17,474 --> 00:04:18,774
[ED] Friend of yours?

56
00:04:18,807 --> 00:04:22,374
[ARMSTRONG]
He's from Central...
A talented State Alchemist.

57
00:04:22,407 --> 00:04:23,540
He was researching into

58
00:04:23,574 --> 00:04:26,440
possible medical
applications of alchemy.

59
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:28,407
But after the
Ishvalan Civil War,

60
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,574
he went missing--
just disappeared.

61
00:04:31,807 --> 00:04:33,440
[ED]
Let's go, major.

62
00:04:33,474 --> 00:04:34,640
A guy like this
doctor might know

63
00:04:34,674 --> 00:04:37,374
some useful things
about bio-alchemy.

64
00:04:41,974 --> 00:04:45,674
[ARMSTRONG]
Excuse me, but do you know who
this person is by any chance?

65
00:04:45,707 --> 00:04:47,607
Wow, major, you
can really draw.

66
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,374
The art of portraiture
has been passed down through

67
00:04:49,407 --> 00:04:51,807
the Armstrong family
for generations.

68
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:53,907
[VILLAGER A]
That man looks like
Dr. Mauro to me.

69
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:54,940
Mauro?

70
00:04:54,974 --> 00:04:56,940
All of our town's doctors
were drafted to help

71
00:04:56,974 --> 00:04:59,307
on the battlefields
during the civil war...

72
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:02,674
Then Dr. Mauro came here.
He's really been a lifesaver.

73
00:05:02,707 --> 00:05:05,907
He'll see any patient and
he never gives up on anybody.

74
00:05:05,940 --> 00:05:07,074
We're lucky he's here.

75
00:05:07,107 --> 00:05:08,874
You see this big,
bright flash of light,

76
00:05:08,907 --> 00:05:10,807
and then you're cured,
just like that!

77
00:05:10,840 --> 00:05:12,874
Hmm...

78
00:05:13,707 --> 00:05:14,707
[ED]
This is it.

79
00:05:17,374 --> 00:05:19,007
Um, hello!

80
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,274
[GUN FIRES]

81
00:05:21,507 --> 00:05:22,207
[MARCOH]
All right... Tell me what
you two are doing here.

82
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,440
Have you come
to take me back?

83
00:05:24,474 --> 00:05:26,707
[ARMSTRONG]
Please, Doctor...
calm down.

84
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:29,674
I don't ever want to go back!
Anything but that!

85
00:05:29,707 --> 00:05:31,440
That's not it.
Please listen.

86
00:05:31,474 --> 00:05:33,474
So you're here
to silence me, then?

87
00:05:33,507 --> 00:05:34,707
No, nothing like that!

88
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:37,307
I won't be tricked by you!

89
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:38,840
[CRASHING SOUND]

90
00:05:38,874 --> 00:05:41,440
I'll ask you one more time:
please, calm down!

91
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:42,974
Alphonse!

92
00:05:46,074 --> 00:05:47,274
[ARMSTRONG]
So, you changed your name and

93
00:05:47,307 --> 00:05:50,840
decided to live in hiding way
out here in the countryside.

94
00:05:50,874 --> 00:05:52,674
If the rumors I've
heard can be believed,

95
00:05:52,707 --> 00:05:53,540
when you
disappeared...

96
00:05:53,574 --> 00:05:56,774
You took top-secret
materials with you.

97
00:05:56,807 --> 00:05:59,607
[MARCOH]
I couldn't handle it anymore.

98
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,074
Order or no order, to
have to dirty my hands

99
00:06:02,107 --> 00:06:04,940
researching that
thing was too much.

100
00:06:04,974 --> 00:06:06,940
What 'thing' is that?

101
00:06:06,974 --> 00:06:09,307
It took so many lives...

102
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:10,140
During the Civil War,

103
00:06:10,174 --> 00:06:14,674
so many innocent
died because of it.

104
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:16,640
I could spend my
whole life trying

105
00:06:16,674 --> 00:06:19,874
and still never atone
for the things I've done.

106
00:06:19,907 --> 00:06:21,440
But I had to do something,

107
00:06:21,474 --> 00:06:22,674
so I came here to be a doctor,

108
00:06:22,707 --> 00:06:26,940
to save lives instead
of taking them.

109
00:06:26,974 --> 00:06:28,940
Doctor...
what exactly was it

110
00:06:28,974 --> 00:06:31,074
you were ordered
to do research on?

111
00:06:31,107 --> 00:06:33,407
What 'thing'?

112
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:34,807
The Philosopher's Stone.

113
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:35,840
[ED AND AL GASP]

114
00:06:37,107 --> 00:06:40,940
The top-secret materials I took
were my research documents...

115
00:06:40,974 --> 00:06:43,074
...and the stone itself.

116
00:06:43,107 --> 00:06:45,974
Do you mean you
still have it? It's here?!

117
00:06:53,807 --> 00:06:56,574
[ED] How can that be
the stone? It's a liquid.

118
00:06:58,907 --> 00:07:00,307
[EVERYONE GASPS]

119
00:07:02,974 --> 00:07:06,474
The Sage's Stone...
The Grand Elixir...

120
00:07:06,507 --> 00:07:09,840
The Celestial Stone...
The Red Tincture...

121
00:07:09,874 --> 00:07:11,607
The Fifth Element...

122
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:14,674
Just as the Philosopher's Stone
is called by many names,

123
00:07:14,707 --> 00:07:19,774
so it can take on many forms...
It is not necessarily a stone.

124
00:07:19,807 --> 00:07:22,340
This is an incomplete
product, however...

125
00:07:22,374 --> 00:07:24,407
There's no way to know when
it will reach its limit

126
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:26,340
and become unusable.

127
00:07:26,374 --> 00:07:28,807
[ED] Finished or not, it
demonstrated plenty of power

128
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,874
during the Ishvalan
Civil War, right?

129
00:07:30,907 --> 00:07:32,174
Huh...?

130
00:07:32,207 --> 00:07:34,974
[ED] It's just like the stone
that false priest had in Liore.

131
00:07:35,007 --> 00:07:36,474
It was incomplete, but it still

132
00:07:36,507 --> 00:07:38,940
amplified his
powers considerably.

133
00:07:40,607 --> 00:07:43,540
If imitation stones this
powerful can be produced,

134
00:07:43,574 --> 00:07:46,340
who's to say a complete
product can't be created?

135
00:07:46,374 --> 00:07:47,674
[THUD]

136
00:07:47,707 --> 00:07:48,640
Please, Dr. Marcoh,

137
00:07:48,674 --> 00:07:52,307
I need access to your
research materials.

138
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:55,307
[MARCOH] Major...
Who exactly is this boy?

139
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:58,407
This boy is
a State Alchemist, doctor.

140
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,507
What?! But he's only a child!

141
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:03,307
[MARCOH GRUNTS]

142
00:08:04,540 --> 00:08:06,540
[MARCOH]
After the war, there were
many State Alchemists

143
00:08:06,574 --> 00:08:08,607
who turned in
their certifications

144
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:12,074
because they refused to serve
as human weapons any more.

145
00:08:12,107 --> 00:08:13,940
And now a child...!

146
00:08:13,974 --> 00:08:17,340
[ED] You think I don't know
what I've signed up for?!

147
00:08:17,374 --> 00:08:19,807
I know what I'm doing,
but I don't have any choice.

148
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:22,040
If this is a mistake, then it's
a mistake I have to make.

149
00:08:22,074 --> 00:08:23,807
There is no other way.

150
00:08:29,740 --> 00:08:32,874
[MARCOH]
I see... So you've
committed the taboo?

151
00:08:34,907 --> 00:08:37,540
Amazing...
the ability to transmute

152
00:08:37,574 --> 00:08:40,474
a specific person's
soul like this.

153
00:08:40,507 --> 00:08:42,674
Maybe one as talented
as you would be able

154
00:08:42,707 --> 00:08:45,540
to produce a complete
Philosopher's Stone.

155
00:08:45,574 --> 00:08:46,274
So...!

156
00:08:46,307 --> 00:08:48,474
But I can't show
you my research.

157
00:08:48,507 --> 00:08:49,507
Why not!?

158
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:51,574
You must not
seek after the stone.

159
00:08:51,607 --> 00:08:53,940
Not even if it's to
get our bodies back?

160
00:08:53,974 --> 00:08:54,874
Never!

161
00:08:54,907 --> 00:08:56,907
This is the
devil's research.

162
00:08:56,940 --> 00:09:00,407
If you chase the stone,
you will go through hell!

163
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,874
I've already
been through hell!

164
00:09:04,407 --> 00:09:06,940
[MARCOH] Please...
Please, just leave.

165
00:09:06,974 --> 00:09:09,374
[HORSE WHINNIES]

166
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:20,807
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

167
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,974
[ED]
I've already been through hell!

168
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,540
[ARMSTRONG]
Are you sure
about this, Ed?

169
00:09:30,574 --> 00:09:31,674
Huh..?

170
00:09:31,707 --> 00:09:34,440
Even an incomplete Philosopher's
Stone could be useful.

171
00:09:34,474 --> 00:09:36,774
You could have taken it
from the doctor by force.

172
00:09:36,807 --> 00:09:40,707
Yeah... I wanted it so badly,
I could almost taste it.

173
00:09:40,740 --> 00:09:42,074
But, still...

174
00:09:42,107 --> 00:09:44,840
But still, we don't want
it so badly that we'd be

175
00:09:44,874 --> 00:09:48,807
willing to deprive this town of
their only doctor to get it.

176
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,607
We gained plenty just
by finding out that

177
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:52,907
the Philosopher's
Stone can be made.

178
00:09:52,940 --> 00:09:55,507
Now we'll just have to look
for some other way to do it.

179
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:56,940
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS]

180
00:09:56,974 --> 00:09:58,640
[ED]
What about you, Major?

181
00:09:58,674 --> 00:10:00,407
How do you feel about
not reporting back

182
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:03,740
to Central on Dr.
Marcoh's location?

183
00:10:03,774 --> 00:10:06,074
I met a simple,
small-town doctor today.

184
00:10:06,107 --> 00:10:08,940
I can't see any real
reason to report that.

185
00:10:08,974 --> 00:10:10,807
[ED LAUGHS]

186
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,007
[MARCOH]
Wait!

187
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:15,274
[MARCOH BREATHES HEAVILY]

188
00:10:16,907 --> 00:10:19,374
[ED]
Dr. Marcoh?

189
00:10:19,407 --> 00:10:21,874
[MARCOH]
This is where
my materials are.

190
00:10:21,907 --> 00:10:23,340
If you're certain
you won't regret

191
00:10:23,374 --> 00:10:24,940
learning the truth
in the end,

192
00:10:24,974 --> 00:10:27,607
start looking here.

193
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:28,674
Look closely...

194
00:10:28,707 --> 00:10:31,974
maybe you'll find the truth
hidden within the truth.

195
00:10:32,007 --> 00:10:35,007
But... I've said
too much already.

196
00:10:36,540 --> 00:10:37,707
[MARCOH] I hope
the day will come

197
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:40,940
when you are able to
restore your bodies.

198
00:10:47,007 --> 00:10:50,407
[AL] Brother...
What does the note say?

199
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:53,707
[ED] National Central
Library, First Branch.

200
00:10:53,740 --> 00:10:54,474
I get it.

201
00:10:54,507 --> 00:10:57,007
Like hiding a tree
in the forest...

202
00:10:57,040 --> 00:10:58,940
Finding one book
in that giant library

203
00:10:58,974 --> 00:11:00,940
will be
difficult indeed.

204
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:05,307
Finally, another clue
about the stone!

205
00:11:08,374 --> 00:11:09,874
[DOOR CREAKS]

206
00:11:09,907 --> 00:11:11,807
[MARCOH SIGHS]

207
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:14,574
[LUST]
I've been looking
for you, Marcoh.

208
00:11:15,974 --> 00:11:17,874
[LUST LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

209
00:11:17,907 --> 00:11:20,040
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

210
00:11:23,490 --> 00:11:25,590
[NARRATOR]
Fullmetal Alchemist.

211
00:11:26,590 --> 00:11:28,857
[DOG BARKS]

212
00:11:31,657 --> 00:11:34,523
[PINAKO]
Winry...! Winry!

213
00:11:34,557 --> 00:11:36,690
Our best customer's here!

214
00:11:37,723 --> 00:11:38,523
Huh..?

215
00:11:38,557 --> 00:11:39,790
[ED]
Yo! Granny!

216
00:11:39,823 --> 00:11:40,957
[AL]
We're home!

217
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:43,590
[PINAKO] Oh dear,
what have you done now?

218
00:11:43,623 --> 00:11:46,057
[ED]
A lot has happened.
Can you fix us up?

219
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:47,757
[LOUD THUD]

220
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:50,290
This is Major Alex
Louis Armstrong.

221
00:11:50,323 --> 00:11:52,257
I'm Pinako Rockbell.

222
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:55,923
I know I haven't seen
you for awhile, Ed...

223
00:11:55,957 --> 00:11:58,890
But you've gone
and grown smaller!

224
00:11:58,923 --> 00:12:00,690
Granny...
you've got it wrong.

225
00:12:00,723 --> 00:12:01,790
You're supposed to say

226
00:12:01,823 --> 00:12:03,857
"how big you've
grown lately, Ed."

227
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,457
But why would I say
something so clearly untrue?

228
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:08,690
I'm still taller than
you, you mini-hag!

229
00:12:09,457 --> 00:12:11,590
[ED YELLS]

230
00:12:11,623 --> 00:12:13,657
Edward, I thought
I told you to call first

231
00:12:13,690 --> 00:12:15,390
when you're heading
back here for maintenance!

232
00:12:15,423 --> 00:12:17,590
Winry! Are you
trying to kill me?!

233
00:12:17,623 --> 00:12:20,890
[WINRY LAUGHS]

234
00:12:20,923 --> 00:12:22,590
Welcome back!

235
00:12:22,623 --> 00:12:23,923
Yeah...

236
00:12:23,957 --> 00:12:26,490
[WINRY] Oh no!

237
00:12:26,523 --> 00:12:28,923
[ED] Yeah, sorry.
It's a little smashed up.

238
00:12:28,957 --> 00:12:30,990
"A little smashed up?"
"A little," Ed?!

239
00:12:31,023 --> 00:12:33,423
Do you see what you've
done to my beautiful creation?!

240
00:12:33,457 --> 00:12:34,723
I slaved over this!

241
00:12:34,757 --> 00:12:37,523
It's basically the same;
it's just in smaller pieces.

242
00:12:37,557 --> 00:12:38,823
[ED YELLS]

243
00:12:38,857 --> 00:12:39,623
Don't tell me...

244
00:12:39,657 --> 00:12:42,057
You a little
smashed up too, Al?

245
00:12:42,090 --> 00:12:43,423
What kind of trouble
have you two been

246
00:12:43,457 --> 00:12:45,623
getting yourselves into?

247
00:12:45,657 --> 00:12:47,790
[AL YELLS]

248
00:12:47,823 --> 00:12:51,357
You idiots!
All you ever do is worry me.

249
00:12:51,390 --> 00:12:53,890
[PINAKO]
All right, I see.

250
00:12:53,923 --> 00:12:55,923
In order to get this
information you need,

251
00:12:55,957 --> 00:12:59,490
you want to go to Central
as soon as possible, am I right?

252
00:12:59,523 --> 00:13:02,890
[ED] Yeah... this is
kind of a rush order.

253
00:13:02,923 --> 00:13:05,523
[PINAKO]
Hmm... it's not just the arm.

254
00:13:05,557 --> 00:13:07,523
Your leg needs adjusting too.

255
00:13:07,557 --> 00:13:10,023
Guess you're growth's not
completely stunted after all.

256
00:13:10,057 --> 00:13:11,023
Oh, shut up!

257
00:13:11,057 --> 00:13:13,590
[PINAKO] The leg aside,
the shape the arm's in,

258
00:13:13,623 --> 00:13:15,690
we'll have to build
it from scratch.

259
00:13:15,723 --> 00:13:17,790
Is there any chance you
can have it done in a week?

260
00:13:17,823 --> 00:13:19,957
[PINAKO]
Give us some credit, Ed.

261
00:13:22,423 --> 00:13:24,390
Three days.

262
00:13:24,423 --> 00:13:27,757
But you'll have to make do
with this spare for now.

263
00:13:29,490 --> 00:13:32,457
It's a little difficult to walk
on a leg I'm not used to.

264
00:13:32,490 --> 00:13:34,923
[PINAKO]
We'll be finished before
you get used to it.

265
00:13:34,957 --> 00:13:36,390
Three days, huh...?

266
00:13:36,423 --> 00:13:37,657
Between machining, assembly,

267
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:39,590
connecting, and finishing...

268
00:13:39,623 --> 00:13:41,423
That's three all-nighters.

269
00:13:41,457 --> 00:13:43,923
I'm sorry for
all the trouble.

270
00:13:43,957 --> 00:13:45,057
Well, you want
to get to Central

271
00:13:45,090 --> 00:13:46,790
as soon as possible, right?

272
00:13:46,823 --> 00:13:48,790
Then I'll work
my butt off for you...

273
00:13:48,823 --> 00:13:49,923
But you better
believe you're gonna

274
00:13:49,957 --> 00:13:52,057
pay a fortune in
rush order fees!

275
00:13:52,090 --> 00:13:52,890
[LOUD THUD]

276
00:13:52,923 --> 00:14:02,457
[ARMSTRONG GRUNTS]

277
00:14:02,490 --> 00:14:04,057
The wood
you requested.

278
00:14:04,090 --> 00:14:05,557
Oh... thank you.

279
00:14:06,790 --> 00:14:09,923
I haven't seen Edward anywhere
around the house in a while.

280
00:14:09,957 --> 00:14:11,023
Yeah...

281
00:14:11,057 --> 00:14:14,290
He said he was going off to
visit his mother's grave.

282
00:14:21,557 --> 00:14:22,690
[PINAKO] Major.

283
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:26,957
What kind of lives are
the boys leading these days?

284
00:14:26,990 --> 00:14:28,557
Hmm?

285
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:31,723
They have yet to send us
so much as a single letter.

286
00:14:31,757 --> 00:14:33,823
Ed and Al are well known
for their alchemy,

287
00:14:33,857 --> 00:14:36,590
even in a high-profile
place like Central...

288
00:14:36,623 --> 00:14:38,390
Sometimes that gets
them into trouble.

289
00:14:38,423 --> 00:14:40,890
They seem to have
a knack for finding it.

290
00:14:40,923 --> 00:14:42,690
But don't worry.
They're all right...

291
00:14:42,723 --> 00:14:45,523
The Elric Brothers
are strong boys.

292
00:14:45,557 --> 00:14:46,990
[PINAKO]
Strong, huh...?

293
00:14:47,023 --> 00:14:49,890
Yes... I think you
could call them that.

294
00:14:51,423 --> 00:14:53,323
I'm curious,
Madam Rockbell...

295
00:14:53,357 --> 00:14:54,523
You speak of
the Elrics as though

296
00:14:54,557 --> 00:14:56,390
they were
your grandsons...

297
00:14:56,423 --> 00:14:57,423
Of course.

298
00:14:57,457 --> 00:15:00,357
I've been watching over
them since they were born.

299
00:15:00,390 --> 00:15:02,357
I'm a friend of
the family, you see.

300
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:05,557
The boys' father is an
old drinking pal of mine.

301
00:15:05,590 --> 00:15:07,523
One day he up
and left the village,

302
00:15:07,557 --> 00:15:10,057
abandoning his
wife and sons.

303
00:15:10,090 --> 00:15:13,523
I don't even know whether
he's alive now or not.

304
00:15:21,457 --> 00:15:25,857
[ARMSTRONG]
Come to think of it, Madam,
where are young Winry's parents?

305
00:15:25,890 --> 00:15:26,923
Gone, Major...

306
00:15:26,957 --> 00:15:29,290
They both died
in the Civil War.

307
00:15:30,823 --> 00:15:33,057
My son and his
wife were surgeons.

308
00:15:33,090 --> 00:15:35,923
They went to the battlefield
to do what they could.

309
00:15:35,957 --> 00:15:39,857
There were never enough doctors
for all the injured soldiers.

310
00:15:39,890 --> 00:15:43,357
It was...
terrible... the war.

311
00:15:43,390 --> 00:15:45,390
Yes, it was indeed.

312
00:15:48,957 --> 00:15:52,790
Oh, looks like it's about time
for me to get supper started.

313
00:15:52,823 --> 00:15:54,457
You look like
you could eat a lot,

314
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:56,423
but don't worry;
there's plenty.

315
00:15:56,457 --> 00:15:59,590
Oh no, please don't trouble
yourself on my account.

316
00:15:59,623 --> 00:16:02,290
[PINAKO]
Food always tastes better
with guests anyway...

317
00:16:02,323 --> 00:16:04,057
We also have an
empty patient's cot

318
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:06,757
and some spare bedding
if you'd like.

319
00:16:06,790 --> 00:16:09,590
The boys don't have anywhere
else to stay but here...

320
00:16:09,623 --> 00:16:13,557
Adding one more guest won't
be any inconvenience to us.

321
00:16:13,590 --> 00:16:15,557
What about the house
they grew up in?

322
00:16:18,890 --> 00:16:20,723
[PINAKO]
It's gone now...

323
00:16:20,757 --> 00:16:24,390
The brothers don't have
any home to return to.

324
00:16:24,423 --> 00:16:25,423
The day they left,

325
00:16:25,457 --> 00:16:28,823
after Ed had gotten
his state certification...

326
00:16:28,857 --> 00:16:31,957
...they burned down
their own house.

327
00:16:31,990 --> 00:16:35,623
My guess is they did it because
with no house to come home to...

328
00:16:35,657 --> 00:16:37,790
...there could be
no turning back.

329
00:16:37,823 --> 00:16:41,390
[DOG WHINES]

330
00:16:42,757 --> 00:16:45,357
Yeah, you're right.

331
00:16:45,390 --> 00:16:46,923
We should head back.

332
00:16:50,990 --> 00:16:51,790
I'm back...

333
00:16:51,823 --> 00:16:53,523
Oh, Edward Elric!

334
00:16:53,557 --> 00:16:55,757
Gyaah!

335
00:16:55,790 --> 00:16:57,557
What unyielding love
to try and bring

336
00:16:57,590 --> 00:16:59,357
your mother back to life!

337
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:01,057
What a tremendous
sacrifice to give up

338
00:17:01,090 --> 00:17:05,457
your arm in order to transmute
your brother's disembodied soul!

339
00:17:05,490 --> 00:17:08,023
What determination to
burn down your own house...!

340
00:17:08,057 --> 00:17:10,790
To make sure...
there was no retreat!

341
00:17:10,823 --> 00:17:11,790
Come Edward...

342
00:17:11,823 --> 00:17:14,390
Allow me to offer you
this comforting embrace!

343
00:17:14,423 --> 00:17:17,557
[ED] Just stay back!
Don't rub your chest on me!

344
00:17:17,590 --> 00:17:18,657
Aahhh!

345
00:17:22,738 --> 00:17:25,971
[ROOSTER CROWS]

346
00:17:26,005 --> 00:17:33,505
[BUZZING SOUND]

347
00:17:37,938 --> 00:17:40,605
[BUZZING SOUND]

348
00:17:41,038 --> 00:17:43,838
Look at you, working hard
so early in the morning.

349
00:17:43,871 --> 00:17:45,538
Been up all night.

350
00:17:50,355 --> 00:17:52,822
Heh, Heh, You're still
at it, busy as a bee.

351
00:17:52,855 --> 00:17:54,989
At this rate,
you must be almost done.

352
00:17:55,022 --> 00:17:57,122
One more all nighter.

353
00:17:57,155 --> 00:17:58,689
Oh.

354
00:18:08,855 --> 00:18:09,722
[THUD]

355
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:10,722
[WINRY]
Get out!

356
00:18:10,755 --> 00:18:11,789
[DOOR SLAMS]

357
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:15,199
[BIRDS CHIRP]

358
00:18:15,199 --> 00:18:17,333
[AL] They said it would
take three days, right?

359
00:18:17,366 --> 00:18:19,433
So, give 'em three days.

360
00:18:19,466 --> 00:18:21,766
[ED]
Yeah, I know, I know...

361
00:18:21,799 --> 00:18:23,699
It's just when I think of
a clue to the stone sitting

362
00:18:23,733 --> 00:18:26,933
in Central library somewhere,
I get so impatient!

363
00:18:28,199 --> 00:18:29,833
[DOG BARKS]

364
00:18:31,033 --> 00:18:33,666
Here you go!
It's all ready!

365
00:18:33,699 --> 00:18:34,699
[WINRY LAUGHS]

366
00:18:36,066 --> 00:18:37,066
[PINAKO] Ready?

367
00:18:37,099 --> 00:18:38,133
Ah...yeah.

368
00:18:38,166 --> 00:18:39,199
On one...

369
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:39,866
Two...

370
00:18:39,899 --> 00:18:40,399
[PINAKO AND WINRY]
Three!

371
00:18:40,433 --> 00:18:43,799
[ED GRUNTS IN AGONY]

372
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:45,133
That's the worst
part every time.

373
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:47,866
When the nerves have
to connect like that.

374
00:18:47,899 --> 00:18:49,366
[ED] Once we have
the Philosopher's Stone,

375
00:18:49,399 --> 00:18:51,766
I can kiss
that pain goodbye!

376
00:18:51,799 --> 00:18:53,333
Our biggest
source of income...

377
00:18:53,366 --> 00:18:55,166
I'll be sad to see you go.

378
00:18:55,199 --> 00:18:56,299
[ED YELLS IN AGONY]

379
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:57,299
Hold still...

380
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,699
Ugh... Do you want me
to do this right or not?

381
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:02,166
It's just so lovely!

382
00:19:02,199 --> 00:19:05,166
The smell of oil!
The hum of the ball bearings!

383
00:19:05,199 --> 00:19:07,133
The rugged yet amazingly
beautiful form

384
00:19:07,166 --> 00:19:09,866
created through
anatomical engineering!

385
00:19:09,899 --> 00:19:13,899
Ah! How wonderful
you are! My automail!

386
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:15,166
Crazy gearhead...

387
00:19:15,199 --> 00:19:18,133
You're lost without me,
alchemy freak.

388
00:19:18,166 --> 00:19:19,866
[PINAKO]
All right. We're done.

389
00:19:22,899 --> 00:19:23,966
Well?

390
00:19:23,999 --> 00:19:25,433
Yeah...
It feels good.

391
00:19:25,466 --> 00:19:27,766
I increased the percentage
of chrome this time,

392
00:19:27,799 --> 00:19:29,966
so it should be
less prone to rusting.

393
00:19:29,999 --> 00:19:31,899
The tradeoff is that it's
not quite as strong,

394
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:33,933
so don't try anything crazy--

395
00:19:33,966 --> 00:19:34,966
Hey! Listen up!

396
00:19:34,999 --> 00:19:36,299
[ED]
Al, it's your turn!

397
00:19:37,299 --> 00:19:39,166
[ARMSTRONG]
You can fix him right here?

398
00:19:39,199 --> 00:19:42,399
Yep... You have to know
the trick to it, though.

399
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:45,399
Major, you see that seal
on the inside of his back?

400
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:48,666
That's the medium between
Al's soul and the armor.

401
00:19:48,699 --> 00:19:51,199
So I have to be
sure not to ruin it.

402
00:19:56,966 --> 00:19:59,799
There you go!
You're good as new!

403
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:01,766
You ready to try it out?

404
00:20:01,799 --> 00:20:02,699
Yeah!

405
00:20:04,399 --> 00:20:07,799
[PINAKO]
It'll be quiet around
here without those boys.

406
00:20:09,466 --> 00:20:10,399
Well, Brother?

407
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:12,666
Yep, it's time to head
to Central and find

408
00:20:12,699 --> 00:20:14,833
Dr. Marcoh's documents.

409
00:20:14,866 --> 00:20:17,166
We leave first thing
tomorrow morning.

410
00:20:20,466 --> 00:20:25,666
[ED SNORES]

411
00:20:29,199 --> 00:20:31,433
Sleeping with his
tummy out again.

412
00:20:31,466 --> 00:20:33,133
What am I gonna do with him?

413
00:20:33,166 --> 00:20:34,666
It's like you're
the older one...

414
00:20:34,699 --> 00:20:35,933
Huh, Al?

415
00:20:35,966 --> 00:20:37,166
He can be a handful.

416
00:20:37,199 --> 00:20:39,399
Someone has to
look after him.

417
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:41,999
[PINAKO]
How old are the two
of you boys now?

418
00:20:42,033 --> 00:20:44,699
[AL] I'm fourteen...
and Brother's fifteen.

419
00:20:47,266 --> 00:20:50,299
To think someone as young
and as small as he is...

420
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:52,299
...could be used
as a human weapon.

421
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:56,899
It's almost funny...
especially watching him sleep.

422
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:59,833
[AL]
Thanks... both of you.

423
00:20:59,866 --> 00:21:02,166
[WINRY]
What's this? Why so formal?

424
00:21:02,199 --> 00:21:04,433
[AL]
Granny, Winry...

425
00:21:04,466 --> 00:21:05,933
I'm so grateful to you for

426
00:21:05,966 --> 00:21:09,166
always welcoming us
like we're really family.

427
00:21:09,199 --> 00:21:11,266
He won't ever say it, but...

428
00:21:11,299 --> 00:21:13,166
I know Brother
feels the same way.

429
00:21:13,199 --> 00:21:14,866
[WINRY] Al...

430
00:21:14,899 --> 00:21:16,133
[PINAKO]
Don't you worry, dear...

431
00:21:16,166 --> 00:21:18,399
We know he feels
that way, too...

432
00:21:18,433 --> 00:21:20,299
He doesn't have to say it.

433
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:23,733
[AL]
Granny... Winry...

434
00:21:23,766 --> 00:21:26,166
...thank you.

435
00:21:28,399 --> 00:21:30,766
Thank you again
for everything, Granny.

436
00:21:30,799 --> 00:21:31,833
[PINAKO] Sure.

437
00:21:31,866 --> 00:21:33,433
[AL] Hey... where's Winry?

438
00:21:33,466 --> 00:21:36,299
[PINAKO]
Resting. She's stayed up
three nights in a row.

439
00:21:36,333 --> 00:21:37,166
Want me to wake her?

440
00:21:37,199 --> 00:21:40,066
No, that's okay...
She'd just nag me.

441
00:21:40,099 --> 00:21:42,766
Make sure to do
maintenance or whatever...

442
00:21:44,199 --> 00:21:45,866
[PINAKO]
Hold on a second, boys.

443
00:21:45,899 --> 00:21:47,133
[ED] Hmm?

444
00:21:47,166 --> 00:21:48,766
You should come back
once in a while

445
00:21:48,799 --> 00:21:50,199
and have dinner with us.

446
00:21:50,233 --> 00:21:52,166
[AL AND ED LAUGH]

447
00:21:52,199 --> 00:21:53,399
You want us to
come all this way

448
00:21:53,433 --> 00:21:55,366
into the mountains
just for some dinner?

449
00:21:55,399 --> 00:21:57,133
[PINAKO LAUGHS]

450
00:21:57,166 --> 00:21:59,733
[WINRY]
Edward...! Alphonse!

451
00:21:59,766 --> 00:22:01,399
Come back soon, 'kay?

452
00:22:05,133 --> 00:22:06,033
[ED] Yeah!

453
00:22:06,066 --> 00:22:07,633
[AL LAUGHS]

454
00:23:44,233 --> 00:23:46,633
[WINRY YAWNS]

455
00:23:47,299 --> 00:23:50,933
I just about slept
through the entire day.

456
00:23:50,966 --> 00:23:54,799
Whenever Ed comes over it's
like a tornado hit this place.

457
00:23:57,199 --> 00:23:58,366
Huh?

458
00:24:00,799 --> 00:24:02,233
Whoopsy...

459
00:24:05,166 --> 00:24:07,199
[NARRATOR]
Doctor Marcoh's notes on
the Philosopher's Stone

460
00:24:07,233 --> 00:24:09,666
were indeed in
the place he said.

461
00:24:09,699 --> 00:24:11,666
But nothing is ever that easy.

462
00:24:11,699 --> 00:24:13,066
Unfortunately for the Elrics,

463
00:24:13,099 --> 00:24:15,399
the enemy is always
one step ahead,

464
00:24:15,433 --> 00:24:17,099
leading the boys
ever deeper into

465
00:24:17,133 --> 00:24:19,999
the maze of "truth
within the truth."

466
00:24:20,033 --> 00:24:23,199
Next time, on Fullmetal
Alchemist: Brotherhood--

467
00:24:23,233 --> 00:24:27,199
Episode Seven. "Hidden Truths."

468
00:24:27,233 --> 00:24:29,266
The only way to
reach the destination

469
00:24:29,299 --> 00:24:31,366
is to never turn away.

